==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Burette
<hw>Bu*rette"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., can,
cruet, dim. of <ets>buire</ets> flagon.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An apparatus for delivering measured quantities of liquid or for
measuring the quantity of liquid or gas received or discharged. It
consists essentially of a graduated glass tube, usually furnished with a
small aperture and stopcock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bur fish</ent>⟦br⟧
